summary:
I am a Museum Professional with international background and experience. 

I was born in Venice (Italy) in 1977, I studied Educational Sciences at the University of Trieste. Before moving to Australia in 2005, I worked in an institution for physically and mentally disabled adults. 

I hold a B.A. in History and Asian Studies from the University of Tasmania (Australia) and  M.A. Cum Laude in Arts and Heritage from the University of Maastricht (The Netherlands).

I have worked for distinguished institutions as the Tasmanian Museum and Art Gallery in Hobart (Australia), the National Maritime Museum in London (UK), and the Taipei National Palace Museum (Taiwan). Beside possessing in-depht knowledge and practical experience in different areas of the museum field, I have received a complete training in World Heritage Administration at the UNESCO World Heritage Centre in Paris (France).

 I am now looking for an opportunity to build up a career in the cultural sector, specializing in the analysis and identification of the best digital solutions for museums and cultural institutions. I am responsible and hard-working. I am a fast learner and like to be part of a team as I greatly value interaction with other professionals.My main strengths are curiosity, dedication, and the determination to supply a qualified service to my employers.

Specialties: Collection care and management, including record-keeping, retrieval of archival data, basic handling and photography;

World Heritage: issues, regulations and administration;

Digital technology and Museums: analysis and identification of best  digital solutions for museums;

